<item>
            <title>[SOLR-15926] Fix version specification in the Solr Ref Guide</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-15926</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently many places use the docs version (major.minor) with .0 added to the end, when we can easily just use the full solr version instead.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There are also instances where the Solr version is used for the lucene version. This needs to be updated now that the two cannot be conflated.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
