                            <comment id="17476694" author="ctargett" created="Sat, 15 Jan 2022 21:08:31 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Currently many places use the docs version (major.minor) with .0 added to the end&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m not sure I&apos;m following this statement - do you have an example where you see where we&apos;re using the major.minor version and tacking on .0 to the end?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Part of me suspects what you&apos;re seeing is simply a wide inconsistency in the part of our various content authors with regard to when and how they refer to a version. In most cases there shouldn&apos;t really be talk about a specific version at all - the Ref Guide is versioned, so there&apos;s no need for things like &quot;Now in 8.8.0...&quot; or &quot;Until 7.7.3...&quot; That stuff should be in the upgrade notes, and the page itself should just talk about how the feature works for that version. I occasionally will edit these out, but don&apos;t have a ton of time for to seek out little things like this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17477840" author="janhoy" created="Tue, 18 Jan 2022 13:10:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I added fixVersion 9.0 - else it will not show up on the blocker list.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17478011" author="houston" created="Tue, 18 Jan 2022 16:15:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=ctargett&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;ctargett&quot;&gt;ctargett&lt;/a&gt; , if you look at &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/solr/pull/526/files#diff-736766bb4450982479955ed3d01af4b36a19a72bedb47983abe7419319b49cadL39&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/solr/pull/526/files#diff-736766bb4450982479955ed3d01af4b36a19a72bedb47983abe7419319b49cadL39&lt;/a&gt; you can see an example. This is a fairly easy thing to fix. I just thought I&apos;d split it out into a separate ticket to track. I plan to do it quickly after I merge the above PR, which includes the logic to make the full version available as a variable in the ref guide. I think most of these are just references to jars and such.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17479556" author="ctargett" created="Thu, 20 Jan 2022 18:10:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Oh, I see what you mean. I&apos;m not sure what I was thinking when I did that (I did it). It seems your change has been merged to main already &lt;del&gt;which would make this done&lt;/del&gt;?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;edit - I did a search and see lots of other places where we do the same thing that you haven&apos;t fixed yet.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17479594" author="houston" created="Thu, 20 Jan 2022 18:43:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have a PR up for the other instances. (Also removing lucene-solr repo links)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17479721" author="ctargett" created="Thu, 20 Jan 2022 22:20:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You know &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=houston&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;houston&quot;&gt;houston&lt;/a&gt;, we could leave this for now and fix it via Antora. Since the version is a core attribute of every document, it&apos;s accessible internally during build time as an inherent attribute (&lt;a href=&quot;https://docs.antora.org/antora/latest/page/intrinsic-attributes/#page-attributes&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://docs.antora.org/antora/latest/page/intrinsic-attributes/#page-attributes&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I was trying to parse the version from the branch name, but Jenkins doesn&apos;t like it so we need to explicitly define the version, which is done in the branch now: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/solr/blob/jira/solr-15556-antora/solr/solr-ref-guide/antora.yml#L6&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/solr/blob/jira/solr-15556-antora/solr/solr-ref-guide/antora.yml#L6&lt;/a&gt;. I tested it with one attribute and it works fine - WDYT?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17479729" author="houston" created="Thu, 20 Jan 2022 22:43:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We can leave this in until antora is merged in, then we can update the PR to use the new method.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17485892" author="mdrob" created="Wed, 2 Feb 2022 15:34:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;One concern here is that previously we didn&apos;t build a new ref guide for every bug-fix release, I think we typically only did it for minor releases. So there might not be a 9.0.1 ref guide, and thus those links might not work - will that be changing with Antora and we&apos;ll plan to build new guides for &lt;b&gt;every&lt;/b&gt; release?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17485918" author="houston" created="Wed, 2 Feb 2022 16:12:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yeah, it&apos;s actually in the release wizard to release the ref guide for every release. That&apos;s the idea.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17485933" author="janhoy" created="Wed, 2 Feb 2022 16:22:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;But that will be a refresh of the existing guide, right? I mean, if the /guide/9_0/ is released and then there is a typo fixed in 9.0.1, we don&apos;t publish a brand new guide on a new URL, we only rebuild everything and the 9_0 one is updated in-place?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17485970" author="houston" created="Wed, 2 Feb 2022 17:10:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, this issue isn&apos;t about renaming the ref guide&apos;s URLs. There are links and usages of the full solr version in the ref-guide pages, that I intend to update to use the version of the latest patch release.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17485975" author="houston" created="Wed, 2 Feb 2022 17:17:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m going to go ahead and merge this so it can be reconciled with the antora work I&apos;m doing. Will merge into the antora branch after the backporting is done.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
